<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-10T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-10T04:00:00-05:00" n="388" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/6:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece (<persName type="from">Morris</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-10T11:00:00+02:00">October 10, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received October 10—6:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>107. Samuel Insull<note n="17" xml:id="d388fn17">Former Chairman of
                                    the Board of Directors of the Middle West Utilities Co. and the
                                    Mississippi Valley Utility Investment Co.</note> just arrested
                                by the police on their own responsibility and is being detained on
                                technical inquiry into his identity and <pb facs="0657" n="553" xml:id="pg_553"/> purpose at Athens. Failing arrival of request
                                for extradition he will be released in 24 hours.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>